   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">A set of tools in the document viewer enables you to view and inspect
            2D and 3D drawings in detail. The options and tools depend on the type of file you
            open.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">In general, after you select a tool, you can continue to use other
            tools along with it. For example, after you select<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Explode Model</uicontrol>, you can use<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Zoom</uicontrol>and<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Orbit</uicontrol>tools. To restore your drawing
            model to the default view, click<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Home</uicontrol>.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The following table provides information on using each of the tools in
            the document viewer.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">
         <table colsep="1" rowsep="1" class="- topic/table ">
            <tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup ">
               <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="20%" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="20%" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <colspec colname="c3" colnum="3" colwidth="60%" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <thead class="- topic/thead ">
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Term</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Icon</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Function</entry>
                  </row>
               </thead>
               <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Pan </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <image href="../../Icons/FV-image4.png"
                               class="- topic/image "
                               placement="inline">
                           <alt class="- topic/alt ">Pan</alt>
                        </image>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Drag to move the drawing or model to a
                                different part of the viewer. </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Zoom </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <image href="../../Icons/FV-image5.png"
                               class="- topic/image "
                               placement="inline">
                           <alt class="- topic/alt ">Zoom</alt>
                        </image>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Perform any of the following options to
                                zoom in or zoom out a drawing model: <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                           <li class="- topic/li ">Click a part of the design and
                                        double-click to zoom. </li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">Click a part of the design and press
                                        CTRL + Down Arrow key to zoom in and CTRL + Up Arrow key to
                                        zoom out. </li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">Click a part of the design and rotate
                                        the wheel button. <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                                 <li class="- topic/li ">Forward or away from user = zoom
                                                out. </li>
                                 <li class="- topic/li ">Backward or towards the user =
                                                zoom in. </li>
                              </ul>
                           </li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Home </uicontrol>to
                                        return to the default view. </li>
                        </ul>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Camera Interactions </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <image href="../../Icons/FV-image17.png"
                               class="- topic/image "
                               placement="inline">
                           <alt class="- topic/alt ">Camera Interactions</alt>
                        </image>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image17.png"
                               class="- topic/image "
                               placement="inline">
                           <alt class="- topic/alt ">Camera Interactions</alt>
                        </image> and then click the type of view you want to use. <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                           <li class="- topic/li ">Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image18.png"
                                     class="- topic/image "
                                     placement="inline">
                                 <alt class="- topic/alt ">Fit to view</alt>
                              </image> to position the model at the center of the
                                        viewport. </li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image19.png"
                                     class="- topic/image "
                                     placement="inline">
                                 <alt class="- topic/alt ">Roll</alt>
                              </image> to rotate the model. </li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">If the file is a 3D model, then click
                                            <image href="../../Icons/FV-image20.png"
                                     class="- topic/image "
                                     placement="inline">
                                 <alt class="- topic/alt ">Adjust Focal length</alt>
                              </image> to change the current camera focal length of the
                                        model. </li>
                        </ul>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Measure </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <image href="../../Icons/FV-image7.png"
                               class="- topic/image "
                               placement="inline">
                           <alt class="- topic/alt ">Measure</alt>
                        </image>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Click to view all the measurement options
                                and then select the appropriate option. When completed, click
                                    <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Done</uicontrol>
                                to turn off the measurement. <p class="- topic/p ">In 2D designs,
                                    you can use the following measurement options:</p>
                        <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                           <li class="- topic/li ">Distance</li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">Angle</li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">Area</li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">Arc</li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">Calibrate</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="- topic/p ">In 3D designs, you can use the following
                                    measurement options:</p>
                        <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                           <li class="- topic/li ">Distance</li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">Angle</li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">Calibrate</li>
                        </ul>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Document Browser </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <image href="../../Icons/FV-image21.png"
                               class="- topic/image "
                               placement="inline">
                           <alt class="- topic/alt ">Document Browser</alt>
                        </image>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">To switch the view between 2D and 3D,
                                perform the following steps: <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                           <li class="- topic/li ">Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image21.png"
                                     class="- topic/image "
                                     placement="inline">
                                 <alt class="- topic/alt ">Document Browser</alt>
                              </image>. <p class="- topic/p ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Document
                                                Browser</uicontrol> dialog box is displayed.</p>
                           </li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Tree </uicontrol>tab,
                                        expand <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Model
                                        </uicontrol>and then click the appropriate view. <note class="- topic/note "> If the document supports only
                                                <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">2D
                                                View </uicontrol>, then the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">3D View
                                            </uicontrol> option is not available. </note>
                           </li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">To view the thumbnails of the drawing,
                                        click the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Thumbnails </uicontrol>tab. </li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">Click the appropriate page. </li>
                        </ol>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Layer Manager </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <image href="../../Icons/FV-image22.png"
                               class="- topic/image "
                               placement="inline">
                           <alt class="- topic/alt ">Layer Manager</alt>
                        </image>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">To view layers in the drawing design,
                                perform the following steps: <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                           <li class="- topic/li ">Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image22.png"
                                     class="- topic/image "
                                     placement="inline">
                                 <alt class="- topic/alt ">Layer Manager</alt>
                              </image>. The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Layers </uicontrol>dialog box is displayed. </li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Layers
                                        </uicontrol>dialog box, click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image23.png"
                                     class="- topic/image "
                                     placement="inline">
                                 <alt class="- topic/alt ">Show/Hide </alt>
                              </image>to show or hide layers in the drawing model. <p class="- topic/p ">Alternatively, in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Enter Filter
                                                Term</uicontrol> box, click and enter the layer name
                                            to search for a layer.</p>
                           </li>
                        </ol>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Properties </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <image href="../../Icons/FV-image10.png"
                               class="- topic/image "
                               placement="inline">
                           <alt class="- topic/alt ">Properties</alt>
                        </image>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Click to view the properties of a selected
                                part within the drawing. </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Full Screen </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <image href="../../Icons/FV-image11.png"
                               class="- topic/image "
                               placement="inline">
                           <alt class="- topic/alt ">Full Screen</alt>
                        </image>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Click to change the viewer to full-screen
                                view. <p class="- topic/p ">Press <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Esc</uicontrol> or click
                                    the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Full
                                        Screen</uicontrol> toggle option to exit full-screen
                                    view.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </tbody>
            </tgroup>
         </table>
      </p>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Tools specific to 3D drawings:</title>
         <p class="- topic/p ">
            <table colsep="1" rowsep="1" class="- topic/table ">
               <tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup ">
                  <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="20%" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                  <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="20%" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                  <colspec colname="c3" colnum="3" colwidth="60%" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                  <thead class="- topic/thead ">
                     <row class="- topic/row ">
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">Term</entry>
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">Icon</entry>
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">Function</entry>
                     </row>
                  </thead>
                  <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                     <row class="- topic/row ">
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">Orbit </entry>
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                           <image href="../../Icons/FV-image24.png"
                                  class="- topic/image "
                                  placement="inline">
                              <alt class="- topic/alt ">Orbit</alt>
                           </image>
                        </entry>
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image24.png"
                                  class="- topic/image "
                                  placement="inline">
                              <alt class="- topic/alt ">Orbit</alt>
                           </image> and then click the appropriate rotate option you want
                                    to use. <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                              <li class="- topic/li ">Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image25.png"
                                        class="- topic/image "
                                        placement="inline">
                                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">Rotate</alt>
                                 </image> to rotate the model. </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image26.png"
                                        class="- topic/image "
                                        placement="inline">
                                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">Rotate and Tilt</alt>
                                 </image> to rotate and tilt the model as needed. </li>
                           </ul>
                        </entry>
                     </row>
                     <row class="- topic/row ">
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">First Person </entry>
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                           <image href="../../Icons/FV-image27.png"
                                  class="- topic/image "
                                  placement="inline">
                              <alt class="- topic/alt ">Navigate in first person</alt>
                           </image>
                        </entry>
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">To navigate through the 3D drawing
                                    model as if you were actually inside the model, perform the
                                    following steps: <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                              <li class="- topic/li ">Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image27.png"
                                        class="- topic/image "
                                        placement="inline">
                                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">Navigate in first
                                                  person</alt>
                                 </image>. The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Navigate in First
                                                Person </uicontrol> dialog box is displayed. </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">Read the navigation instructions,
                                            and then click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Ok, Got It
                                            </uicontrol>. </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">Navigate through the 3D model using
                                            the following options: <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                                    <li class="- topic/li ">Use the directional keys on
                                                  the keyboard to navigate through your model.
                                                  Alternatively, you can use the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">W A S
                                                  D</uicontrol> keys as the directional keys. <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                                          <li class="- topic/li ">↑ or W - move forward </li>
                                          <li class="- topic/li ">↓ or S - move back </li>
                                          <li class="- topic/li ">← or A - move left </li>
                                          <li class="- topic/li ">→ or D - move right </li>
                                       </ul>
                                    </li>
                                    <li class="- topic/li ">Use Shift + directional keys
                                                  to move faster. </li>
                                    <li class="- topic/li ">To adjust the walk speed,
                                                  use the + or - keys. </li>
                                    <li class="- topic/li ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Home</uicontrol> to return to the default view.
                                                </li>
                                 </ul>
                              </li>
                           </ol>
                        </entry>
                     </row>
                     <row class="- topic/row ">
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">Section Analysis </entry>
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                           <image href="../../Icons/FV-image28.png"
                                  class="- topic/image "
                                  placement="inline">
                              <alt class="- topic/alt ">Section Analysis</alt>
                           </image>
                        </entry>
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image28.png"
                                  class="- topic/image "
                                  placement="inline">
                              <alt class="- topic/alt ">Section Analysis</alt>
                           </image> and then click the type of sectioning you want to use.
                                        <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                              <li class="- topic/li ">Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image29.png"
                                        class="- topic/image "
                                        placement="inline">
                                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">Section along x-axis</alt>
                                 </image> to section along the x-axis. </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image30.png"
                                        class="- topic/image "
                                        placement="inline">
                                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">Section along y-axis</alt>
                                 </image> to section along the y-axis. </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image31.png"
                                        class="- topic/image "
                                        placement="inline">
                                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">Section along z-axis</alt>
                                 </image> to section along the z-axis. </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image32.png"
                                        class="- topic/image "
                                        placement="inline">
                                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">Section a specific
                                                  area</alt>
                                 </image> to section a specific area. </li>
                           </ul>
                           <p class="- topic/p ">Drag the desired manipulators until the
                                        model is sectioned the way you want it. When done, click
                                            <image href="../../Icons/FV-image28.png"
                                     class="- topic/image "
                                     placement="inline">
                                 <alt class="- topic/alt ">Section Analysis</alt>
                              </image> again to turn off sectioning.</p>
                        </entry>
                     </row>
                     <row class="- topic/row ">
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">Explode Model </entry>
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                           <image href="../../Icons/FV-image34.png"
                                  class="- topic/image "
                                  placement="inline">
                              <alt class="- topic/alt ">Explode Model</alt>
                           </image>
                        </entry>
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">To take apart a 3D drawing design and
                                    see the parts that make up the model, perform the following
                                    steps: <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                              <li class="- topic/li ">Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image34.png"
                                        class="- topic/image "
                                        placement="inline">
                                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">Explode Model</alt>
                                 </image>. A slider <image href="../../Icons/FV-image35.png"
                                        class="- topic/image "
                                        placement="inline">
                                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">Slider</alt>
                                 </image> is displayed. </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">Drag the slider forward to separate
                                            the parts of the model. </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">Drag the slider backward to bring
                                            the model back together. </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">Optionally, use <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Zoom</uicontrol>
                                            to take a closer look at a part. </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image34.png"
                                        class="- topic/image "
                                        placement="inline"/> again to go back to the
                                            default view. </li>
                           </ol>
                        </entry>
                     </row>
                     <row class="- topic/row ">
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">Model Browser </entry>
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                           <image href="../../Icons/FV-image37.png"
                                  class="- topic/image "
                                  placement="inline">
                              <alt class="- topic/alt ">Model Browser</alt>
                           </image>
                        </entry>
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">To view or hide a model in the
                                    drawing, perform the following steps: <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                              <li class="- topic/li ">Click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image37.png"
                                        class="- topic/image "
                                        placement="inline">
                                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">Model Browser</alt>
                                 </image>. The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Model</uicontrol>
                                            dialog box is displayed. </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Model</uicontrol>
                                            dialog box, click <image href="../../Icons/FV-image23.png"
                                        class="- topic/image "
                                        placement="inline">
                                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">Show/Hide</alt>
                                 </image> to show or hide a complete model or the parts
                                            in the drawing design. </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Search</uicontrol> box, click and enter the name of
                                            the part that you want to search. </li>
                           </ol>
                        </entry>
                     </row>
                  </tbody>
               </tgroup>
            </table>
         </p>
